    <p>If your subject extends off the side of the photo:<br /><img alt="" src="images/sideinstructions1.jpg" /><br />then, when outlining the subject, move your cursor up to the edge:<br /><img alt="" src="images/sideinstructions2.jpg" /><br />and then off the photo back round to where the subject hits the edge of the photo:<br /><img alt="" src="Images/SideInstructions3.jpg" /><br />The tagger will now join the points where you left and entered the photo.</p><p>Should you wish to tag a photo where the subject is in the corner of the picture, you will need to move the cursor off the edge of the picture then over the corner and then back to where the subject joins the photo. This way the tagger will join the line round the person from where they meet the side, to the corner and then back to where they meet the side again.</p><a href="javascript:history.go(-1)"><-- Back to photo</a>
